The depth-two HBO test advances both producer and consumer pointers from
zero to one while both counts return to zero.  The full condition stays
clear.  The queue therefore accepts its configuration and PUSH, but a
consumer removes the token before the first CPU query.

Keep queue 7 disabled after clearing and configuring it, then repeat the
depth-two SemaHub PUSH/POP test.  The FIFO data path and channel should be
unable to consume a token while FIFO START is zero.  Record channel 3's raw
state before PUSH, immediately afterward, and after the bounded poll.

Restore Valve's queue depth and enable state on every completed cleanup
path.  No descriptor is submitted and no NAND command or media data is
accessed.

---
 drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c | 25 +++++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c b/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/marvell_nand.c
